<b>Subject:</b> another way around this...Grouping!<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=1769" TARGET=_self>C'mon, Geiger. Get it through your head.</A> (Garbonzo)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>If they made it so that if you were in a group with people of the race that the city was, example an ogre with a group of wood elves in Kelenith, then the guards of that city will NOT kill them. Then if we could get my diplomancy ideas i posted down below instigated if any one from the town was to kill them the group could go to the local Gov't to see if anything could be done about it hehe :)

<P>&gt; Verant will never, never, never, never, never, never, never,
<BR>&gt; never allow people to be put into a PvP situation without their
<BR>&gt; express consent.
<P>&gt; Think about your suggestion. That would mean any
<BR>&gt; "good" race who wants to go to Guk gets gang-banged
<BR>&gt; when they enter Innothule. Same with Cazic and Ferrott.
<P>&gt; Also, consider the faction-raising MOBs you can kill to gain
<BR>&gt; access into human areas. A Troll or Ogre can get into Freeport
<BR>&gt; by killing enough Orcs, then turning in belts. This would
<BR>&gt; eliminate this possibility as well.
<P>&gt; Verant won't do it, man.
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
